.TH echo-cli 1  "echo-cli 0.1.0" 
.SH NAME
echo\-cli \- Echo developer CLI
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBecho\-cli\fR [\fB\-\-format\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR] [\fB\-V\fR|\fB\-\-version\fR] <\fIsubcommands\fR>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Echo developer CLI
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-format\fR \fI<FORMAT>\fR [default: text]
Output format (text or json)
.br

.br
\fIPossible values:\fR
.RS 14
.IP \(bu 2
text: Human\-readable text output
.IP \(bu 2
json: Machine\-readable JSON output
.RE
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help (see a summary with \*(Aq\-h\*(Aq)
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
Print version
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
echo\-cli\-verify(1)
Verify hash integrity of a WSC snapshot
.TP
echo\-cli\-bench(1)
Run benchmarks and format results
.TP
echo\-cli\-inspect(1)
Inspect a WSC snapshot
.SH VERSION
v0.1.0
